{
  "doc_id": "36696",
  "text": "Intravenous methylprednisolone 1 g daily for 5 days is the first-line therapy. Nakamura et al. [CITATION_1] suggested a neuroprotective effect of high-dose steroids when given within first 2-3 days after onset of optic neuritis. Many severe NMO attacks respond inadequately to corticosteroid treatment. Plasma exchange and intravenous immunoglobulin were also tried for acute attacks.",
